<p>I need some help with querying XML data in SQL Server 2012. I have a database that has a table <code>Parameters_XML</code> with columns</p>  <pre><code>id, application, parameter_nr flag, value </code></pre>  <p>The <code>parameter_nr</code> is for eg 1 and the value for that parameter is the following: </p>  <pre><code>&lt;Root&gt;   &lt;Row&gt;     &lt;Item id="341" flags="1"&gt;       &lt;Str&gt;2&lt;/Str&gt;     &lt;/Item&gt;     &lt;Item id="342" flags="1"&gt;       &lt;Str&gt;10&lt;/Str&gt;     &lt;/Item&gt;     &lt;Item id="2196" flags="1"&gt;       &lt;Str&gt;7REPJ1&lt;/Str&gt;     &lt;/Item&gt;   &lt;/Row&gt; &lt;/Root&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I need to retrieve the values for all the applications where the item is 341, 342 and 2196. </p>  <p>Eg: for the application 1 the value for the item 341 is 2 and so on.</p>  <p>So far I have written the following query: </p>  <pre><code>SELECT cast (value as XML).value('data(/Root/Row/Item[@id="431"],') FROM Parameters_Xml x WHERE parameter_nr = 1 </code></pre>  <p>But I get the following error: </p>  <blockquote>   <p>Msg 174, Level 15, State 1, Line 1<br>   The value function requires 2 argument(s).</p> </blockquote>  <p>Please help me with a valid query for my needs and some information on why my query is not valid.</p>  <p>Thank you very much for your time.</p>